        </div>
        <p>This episode compares oceanic life in the Arctic and Antarctica. The winter in these regions brings temperatures of minus 50 Â°C and frozen seas that create the biggest challenge. However, there are polynyas in the Arctic, which are free of ice owing to the pressure of currents on either side, and such places do provide refuge for some species, like the walrus and the bowhead whale.
        </p>
